      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARVUE (4) looks very well placed. She's in great form of late, beating a deep field last start at Flemington in solid time. She's proven she's capable of leading or taking a sit but the lead looks hers for the taking here and this isn't much harder at all. Out to 2500m is no issue, expect she takes plenty of catching. STEEL RUN (5) presents third up having made nice improvement last time when out to 2500m at Flemington, beaten under a length by Berkeley Square. He can peak now and go a couple better. ARUGAMAMA (3) was good fresh but struggled when in the market in the G3 Lord Reims at Morphettville last time out. She's right up to winning this on her day and can improve. GARACHICO (1) just found Berkeley Square too strong last time when sent around big odds but comes under notice now. FLAMIN' ROMANS (6) next best.",
